### 03_Prepare_sentinel1_features

This MATLAB tutorial script demonstrates how preprocessed Sentinel-1 SAR-derived features are prepared for LSTM-based water level estimation.

In the associated study, Sentinel-1-derived variables extracted from detected water pixels were used as input features, including σ⁰VH, σ⁰VV, incidence angle, and Day of Year (DOY). 
Ground-based water level observations were used as the target variable.

This script illustrates how the final preprocessed Sentinel-1 feature files are loaded, how key input variables are selected, and how they are synchronized with ground-based 
water level observations using station ID and date-time information. The resulting table represents a model-ready dataset for subsequent LSTM-based water level estimation.
